76561198023809578,Recommended,324260,15664802,"Posted: 2 May, 2015",all,Dr. Rockso,"Reminds me a lot of an old game called ""Solar Winds"", but done in more of a Freespace 2 style in top-down.This game is a lot ""friendlier"" than the 'X' series of space sims with a much less brutal learning curve, although (at this time) you also can't expand as far as with 'X'... the difference is comperable to ""Terraria"" versus ""Minecraft"", both are great games and one is clearly in the spirit of the other, but they're also great games for entirely different reasons. This is an excellent little game for the price, easy to jump into and put lots of hours in, the combat is simplistic yet nuanced, the interface is simple but elegant, and there's plenty of exploring to be had.The game also has an active modding community that adds a steady stream of new content, with obligatory Star Wars and Star Trek ships (screw it, load 'em both and see for yourself which ships are better).  I'm not done with the game yet, but after about 10 hours I can say it was worth grabbing.  Highly recommend."
