76561198103890981,Recommended,324260,32678940,Posted: 23 June,all,Hebus Jebus,"Overall, I would give this game a 7/10.Void expanse's fighting and money making mechanics are... underwhelming. Most of the game is spent grinding up asteroids and running from hordes of pirates.But where Void Expanse really shines in is its storyline. There are currently 3 factions with individual storylines. However, once you've spent hours of grinding to get the weapons and things to complete one faction, you must start from scratch to do the other factions (thats where some cheats come in LOL). The storyline really catches you and makes you understand the type of people your working with. Order, a group of militant warriors planning to defeat the antagionist with brute force. Freedom, group of mercinaries who are interested in escaping void expanse. And of corse, the Fanatics (my favorite story wise). The fanatics are a group of people who worship the antagonist as their gods. But you learn what their leader really thinks.Each story has it's own ending that makes you feel like all the work was worth it.Once again (because I can't say this enough) It is quite a breathtaking story that is worth your time and money, to follow."
