76561197965965295,Recommended,324260,21065330,"Posted: 8 February, 2016",all,Tibbnak,"An interesting 2d top down space sandbox with elements resembling single ship space pirates and zombies, Eve, and a little system shock 2, replete with that new-car indie smell.You generate a galaxy, pick what class's skill package you want to start with, and are dropped in the starting system and offered a tutorial.There are a variety of ship types and weapon types to choose from, various techs to find, and a number of factions of varying difficulty to join.How you gain experience and money is up to you;You can visit stations and talk to npcs to try and get odd jobs,go around hacking old alien ruins floating around for stuff to sell/turn in for science points,go around fragging pirates randomly,trading goods between stations,or hunting down valuable resources hidden in asteroids.The combat has been harkened in other reviews to be like ""Ice skating motorcycle duels"" and that's KINDA true. It's more remenicent of 2d top down naval battles, where each of your weapons have their own arcs and you have a radar you can use to fight things off screen with guided weaponry, and you're sliding along space trying to avoid getting shot up too hard. It's ok.My only gripe is that it's easy to get in over your head, and dying isn't the end, and the game is very grindy.See, the game constantly autosaves, and you aren't allowed to make your own saves. The game is effectively ironman, so if you die then you die. You get deducted a small amount of money and are respawned inside the nearest friendly station.This may sound like a good thing, except for your super expensive investiture of a ship being completely gone for good as well as its contents. You have to buy up the (thankfully free) civilian junk and start from scratch. It's a lot like EVE in this way.Which has the major downside of runing into the grind wall that the game seems to be.  You get such a small trickle of money for the effort that you put into the game that it often is faster to just start a new galaxy and start from scratch rather than grind from a civ ship back up to where you died.There's also a few interesting mods on the workshop, most are russian with (mostly) english translation."
