76561197967471651,Recommended,324260,22722126,"Posted: 30 April, 2016",all,Russell,"A fun game that's essentially a mish mash over other games in the same genre. The graphics are nice and very clean. The game itself is overall enjoyable and fun, but suffers from two big problems there are both related: a lack of pacing and a lack of things to do. When you first start the game you'll already be able to purchase the equipment you'll be using for the vast majority of the game. All that's left is a grind. The games it was inspired by, like Space Rangers and SPAZ, feel a lot more like a stair step of progress - whereas this game feels more like one giant leap.It's an enjoyable leap, but mostly one that's probably only going to appeal to fans of the genre who are just looking for a fresh coat of paint on ideas that are not particularly fresh. That said this is also only for playing single player. This game in many ways seems to have been designed with multiplayer in mind, so if you're into that it may be that it significantly expands the horizons of the game."
