76561198064373133,Recommended,324260,22505767,"Posted: 18 April, 2016",all,Ysthrall,"I picked this game up on sale, as a simple space shoot-em-up. It's actually pretty good, in a happily retro fashion. Theres a small amount of NPC interaction, quite a bit of upgrading space ships and equipment, and the possibility of being fairly successful via trading or mining if you really want to. I went for what certinaly feels like the majority of the game, shooting stuff. User interface is simple, combat can be swift and brutal, and you can certainly tailor your ship and tactics to playstyle. I've seen some complaints that the character advancement doesn't make much difference. It does, but not a lot. By the time you finish the game one way or another, I suspect that you'll be using gameplay skills 30%, equipment 50% and character skills 20%.Still, a good game if you fancy swooping around shooting aliens. Easy to drop in and out of. Fairly addictive."
