,Recommended,324260,19680061,"Posted: 13 December, 2015",all,Silent Snow,"This game might not be perfect, but it certainly is an overlooked gem. I have a somewhat strange fascination with rogue-likes/lites. I also quite enjoy a nice space exploration game. I quite like this game and I keep coming back. Not all games get the formula right, but I think this one does. Some people might say that this game is too easy. I wouldln't know, I find it just right. I am playing it on Normal difficulty though so your mileage may vary.Graphically, it looks decent enough. It's 3D models and particle effects are quite beautiful with lovely backdrops. I would say though that perhaps the backdrops are a bit too colourful. Most of space is empty and black, and I find it hard to believe that you'd see this other huge galaxy in the distance. Sure it would still be millions of light years away, but isn't very realistic. That isn't to say that I don't appreciate them, I do. It makes it seem a bit less bleak than space normally would be.The music holds up, and gives your ears something to listen to although I didn't much care for the music at the start screen. I like the sound design. Although, the ships don't actually have that much difference in engines and the various other effects are the same if you have a Level 1 or Level 3 Laser.In my current run, I find that Laser Energy weapons are by far the best and easiest to aim. A lot of it comes down to the ship though. There are various types of those. I haven't tried Multiplayer yet, but when I do, I will be sure to comment on it.The story is the same, but the destinations are procedurally generated. There are various types of missions. Rescue, Mining, Delivering Packages, Intel, a few mini-games in hacking Enerak terminals.I discovered that running out of fuel wasn't the end of the world, but you travelled a lot slower, even whilst cruising. Without fuel, your ship is severely exposed and crippled. You have no energy for weapons or shields, but you can still live to fight another day.Is it a perfect game? No. I found a few glitches mostly to do with the autosaving message (it is a bit offscreen, I am playing at 4K. I also found that sometimes when you dock with the autopilot or not, the ship circles around the object a bit swirling closer and closer in and then eventually docking.Overally, I really like this game. There is something about exploring space, fighting pirates, mining, and buying parts for your ship to upgrade it. If you enjoy rogue-likes/-lites then you'll enjoy this."
