76561197976525405,Recommended,324260,15258378,"Posted: 7 April, 2015",all,ComGaunt,"Wonderful topdown Elite clone with RPG elements of a skill tree for your character and the customization of your space ship.The combat is similar to Subspace, not sure if anyone remembers that old space combat multiplayer game from the 90's.Your ships have hardpoints which can be fixed (you have to turn your ship to aim) or are turrets that turn a certain amount of degrees and you can aim that way.  Either way,  turning the ship around quickly is important and when things get more difficult your skill (not the skill of your character) of piloting your craft will make a big difference.The fact that the combat is realtime and dependent upon your piloting skill can make the game more frustrating than for example Drox operative which is turn based and the combat is similar to SPAZ.I am 7.5 hours into my second campaign, my character is level 32 and I am enjoying the game immensely by just farming pirates. I have read some of the negative reviews and I agree that the game probably needs more content but otherwise it is perfect for me. I did encounter two crashes so far which is very annoying.Pros:- Open world ""feels"" open-RPG skills work for unlocking weapons/ships and make your character more effective. I would have been happy with justthe ""RPG"" system of upgrading my ship so the added bonus of having a skill tree is awesome- Combat is fun, I enjoy ploughing through  hordes of pirates/aliens- The different weapon systems and energy/kinetic weapons work well... seems balanced/make sense- Ship customization is fun, there are a lot of combination to try. The hull is just another equipment slot so you caneasily swap ships if you want to change from your combat vessel to your mining vessel with more cargo space.- Hunting pirates, mining, trading is easy to do.. all you need to do is find pirates, asteroids and space stations and you are off.- Mods, I can't wait for the game to be out longer and having more mods to install :)- Price, great value for $15Cons:- Needs more content, under extras on the main menu there is an ""upcoming"" button which lists all the things the dev is planning so I think we are good... also the mods will help- Difficulty can  be frustrating sometimes"
