,Not Recommended,324260,23482179,"Posted: 10 June, 2016",all,monsterfurby,"I refunded the game after a fairly short time playing, but let me point out that its core gameplay seems solid. However, the simplistic look combined with the static nature of the galaxy make VoidExpanse basically just another top-down-view space trading sim. The game would be a shoo-in for a feature like dynamic factions and borders, but instead, even though the map is generated, factions remain static in their starting positions and never expand or fight.The leveling system is pretty well done, with fairly interesting skill trees, but doesn't really add much to a game that is, ultimately, very empty.Several years ago, this would have been a worthy competitor to Escape Velocity Nova and similar games, but with newer, more dynamic games like Drox Operative on the market, I feel that, unfortunately VoidExpanse doesn't really add anything that others don't already do better."
