76561197986443427,Not Recommended,324260,15225263,"Posted: 5 April, 2015",all,Rackminster,"I appreciate the work that goes into an Indie title, but that doesn't mean I'm automatically going to recommend it because it's Indie and an impressive effort for that alone.  I don't regret the purchase simply because it's a 'value' title.  If I had to choose again, I would have saved the money and spent it elsewhere.Disclaimer: I have not beaten this game - but in 7 hours of play I did get to level 34 and have explored a large number of sectors.  I'm going to continue for a while and will revise my review if anything compelling happens to alter my feelings.The Good:Ships are customizableOpen galaxy to exploreWell planned character skill treeAttractive backdrops and workable graphicsDevices make for some worthwhile combos - like mining for ore and using it for repairsAutopilot works wellA solid Indie effortThe Meh:Weapons aren't well balanced and lasers rule combatEnemies don't aggro unless you're within a short rangeEnemies largely sit in one spot and wait for you to come kill themMissions and combat are extremely repetitiveA fair number of possible ships and equipment to choose from, but only a few worth usingAutopilot used extensively to get around - you watch the game play itself while you travelLevels come pretty quickly and end up feeling less important for thatThe Bad:The universe feels largely unalive and soulless - it feels like a paint the by numbers adventure kitCombat is soggy as you have to compensate for ship momentum and weapon arcsAI ""Allies"" are dumb as bricks and very much in the way instead of helping"
76561197965588514,Not Recommended,324260,15272169,"Posted: 8 April, 2015",all,Thunderballs,"NOTE: I edit my original view based on my disatisfaction at  the current state of multiplayer, and my doubt that there will ever be a viable multiplayer experience in this game.The game mechanics simply don't allow for a fulfilling multiplayer experience. If you are interested in single player, pick this up on sale. If your intent is to play with friends on a private server, go for it. If however, you are looking for an ongoing, stable community, that allows open sandbox gameplay as the game is designed to accomodate, don't buy. All servers are player hosted, subject to admin abuse, subject to server ruleset constraints. There is no dedicated server sponsored by the developers."
